# Trig identities

Basic trig functions
- sin(x) = opposite/hypotenuse (SOH) = tan(x)cos(x)
- cos(x) = adjacent/hypotenuse (CAH) = sin(x)/tan(x)
- tan(x) = opposite/adjacent   (TOA) = sin(x)/cos(x)

sin and cos are out of phase from each other by π/2
- sin θ = cos(θ ± π/2)
- cos θ = sin(θ ± π/2)


tangens
- tan θ = sin θ / cos θ
- cos θ = sin θ / tan θ
- sin θ = tan θ cos θ

unit circle
- cos²θ + sin²θ = 1
- cos²θ + sin²θ = 1
- sin²θ = 1 - cos²θ
- cos²θ = 1 - sin²θ
